50|$|The <b>negative</b> <b>resistance</b> {{oscillator}} {{model is}} not limited to one-port devices like diodes but can also be applied to feedback oscillator circuits with two port devices such as transistors and tubes. In addition, in modern high frequency oscillators, transistors are increasingly used as one-port <b>negative</b> <b>resistance</b> devices like diodes. At microwave frequencies, transistors with certain loads applied to one port can become unstable due to internal feedback and show <b>negative</b> <b>resistance</b> at the other port. So high frequency transistor oscillators are designed by applying a reactive load to one port to give the transistor <b>negative</b> <b>resistance,</b> and connecting the other port across a resonator to make a <b>negative</b> <b>resistance</b> oscillator as described below.|$|E
